Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.61,0:38:40.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And they all thought I was a little bit crazy.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:42.82,0:38:48.13,Default,,0,0,0,,But if you're not interested enough in love to enjoy a cat's purr, a dog's wagging tail.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.32,0:38:54.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Then all your problem is you're just completely egocentric.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:55.03,0:39:02.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody needs something and someone to love and to love back and to reflect that love as a prevailing reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.59,0:39:04.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, what's next here?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.38,0:39:06.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, wow.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.34,0:39:09.84,Default,,0,0,0,,This must be the great books of the Western world.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:11.53,0:39:12.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that what it is?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:13.03,0:39:14.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, great books in the Western world.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:16.13,0:39:19.44,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a university based on the great books of the Western world.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.94,0:39:21.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Which we'll mention again later.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.73,0:39:34.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The most important thing on this for our for our culture is where is Marx and Engels?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:34.32,0:39:34.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:35.53,0:39:35.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.48,0:39:39.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, here.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.09,0:39:39.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.38,0:39:42.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, because that demarcates a certain level.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.75,0:39:50.34,Default,,0,0,0,,A very important level in the evolution of our world and our culture and politics.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:50.34,0:39:54.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So that'll arise later.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.82,0:39:57.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It's important to know that Marx calibrates at 130.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.32,0:40:08.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, because later on we're going to calibrate institutions, which have become sort of programmed with Marxian concepts.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:08.57,0:40:11.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And we'll notice that they calibrate very low.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.67,0:40:11.98,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.98,0:40:14.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So the reason is Marx is at 130.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.48,0:40:15.98,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why they calibrate low.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.98,0:40:16.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.07,0:40:17.67,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.53,0:40:20.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And here we got market market.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.23,0:40:24.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Machiavelli and various bad actors over time.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.50,0:40:31.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it's very interesting to look at the great books of the Western world.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.88,0:40:35.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Plato at 485.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:36.98,0:40:40.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Shakespeare 465.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.88,0:40:42.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Adam Smith.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:42.38,0:40:45.19,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the wealth of Nations or the wealth of Nations.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:45.48,0:40:47.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Adam Smith is very important in America.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:47.98,0:40:48.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:49.44,0:40:51.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Although you may not have heard of him.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.15,0:40:53.05,Default,,0,0,0,,But he is of great importance.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:53.90,0:41:01.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So I think this is of extreme benefit to students to be familiar.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:01.69,0:41:12.67,Default,,0,0,0,,To just know that such a map, such a map of the great books of the Western world exists because it gives you something.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.17,0:41:17.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Freud is at 499 or Freud was at 499.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.11,0:41:21.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.90,0:41:23.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Freud was at 499.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.51,0:41:26.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's the top of the intellect.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:27.26,0:41:32.69,Default,,0,0,0,,My psychoanalyst, when I was in analysis, calibrates over 499, 500.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.23,0:41:35.73,Default,,0,0,0,,He calibrated 499.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:35.84,0:41:40.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So my psychoanalyst, I had a classical psychoanalysis going on four or five years.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:40.94,0:41:41.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I forget what.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:42.84,0:41:44.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And that was at 499.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.53,0:41:45.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It's good to know.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.44,0:41:45.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:46.23,0:41:47.13,Default,,0,0,0,,That's where it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:48.63,0:41:49.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:49.53,0:41:49.94,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:49.94,0:41:51.23,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll move on to the next.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.13,0:41:53.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.82,0:41:56.63,Default,,0,0,0,,This has to do with the way the brain functions.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.42,0:42:02.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, throughout evolution, we have inherited a left brain and a right brain.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.51,0:42:06.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And it makes quite a bit of difference.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.67,0:42:11.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether you process things through the left brain or the right brain.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:12.03,0:42:21.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And below 200, below consciousness level 200, the left brain is in charge.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:21.61,0:42:24.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's mainly concerned with fight or flight.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.34,0:42:31.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And, uh, has to do with stress and disease and negative muscle tests.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:33.21,0:42:34.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Below 200, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.03,0:42:43.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Below 200, when I press down on her arm, if it calibrates below 200, her arm goes weak.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:43.67,0:42:46.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's a biologic response.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.67,0:42:47.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Biologic.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:47.57,0:42:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not arbitrary.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:50.01,0:42:54.51,Default,,0,0,0,,A negative muscle test response indicates below 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:55.80,0:42:56.19,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.19,0:42:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,That's very important.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.80,0:42:58.61,Default,,0,0,0,,That's very important to know.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:59.30,0:43:04.38,Default,,0,0,0,,On the positive side, above 200, is the right brain.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:04.88,0:43:10.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, the right brain, the left brain puts out, uh, alarm reaction, adrenaline.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:11.00,0:43:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And, uh, things having to do with fright and rage.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:15.03,0:43:19.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Above consciousness level 200, the right brain dominates.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:20.07,0:43:23.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And you have, uh, positive emotion.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:24.23,0:43:27.23,Default,,0,0,0,,You also have greater healing, greater immunity.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:27.73,0:43:34.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, the higher the level of consciousness, the greater your resistance to disease of all kinds.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:34.23,0:43:34.73,Default,,0,0,0,,You know?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:35.55,0:43:36.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.05,0:43:36.55,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll go.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.55,0:43:39.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Any questions about, uh, what we've said?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:40.53,0:43:41.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Better not have any.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:44.59,0:43:45.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Better not, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:48.23,0:43:49.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The impact.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.73,0:43:53.73,Default,,0,0,0,,The levels of consciousness and the social problems.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.23,0:43:56.23,Default,,0,0,0,,See, so it's not just academic.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:56.23,0:43:57.73,Default,,0,0,0,,It's of great importance.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:58.84,0:43:59.34,Default,,0,0,0,,As you can see.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:59.34,0:44:02.34,Default,,0,0,0,,The level of consciousness is 600 and over.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:04.15,0:44:05.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Unemployment is zero.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:05.65,0:44:06.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Crime is zero.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:06.65,0:44:07.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Poverty is zero.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:08.15,0:44:10.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Happiness is 100%.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:13.28,0:44:16.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And the rate of criminality is 0%.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:16.78,0:44:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:18.13,0:44:21.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So, if you got somebody working for you, the best thing to do is calibrate them.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:24.13,0:44:28.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Tells you whether you gotta lock up your money or you can leave it around loose on the table.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:30.30,0:44:31.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Level of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:32.51,0:44:33.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, as you.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:33.51,0:44:37.51,Default,,0,0,0,,As it goes up, you see, unemployment becomes zero.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:37.51,0:44:39.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Poverty is zero.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.61,0:44:41.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Unhappiness is zero.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:42.57,0:44:50.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And as the level of consciousness goes down, you see the rate of unemployment, uh, uh, skyrockets.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:51.07,0:44:57.57,Default,,0,0,0,,When you get to the lower levels of consciousness, you see that unemployment is about 50%.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:58.36,0:45:01.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The rate of poverty is already about 25%.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:02.48,0:45:02.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Low.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:02.98,0:45:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Only 10 or 15% of people think life is okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:07.26,0:45:10.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And the rate of criminality is about 50%.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:10.26,0:45:11.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:12.80,0:45:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So you can see, not all of mankind's problems can be solved by passing a law.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:19.78,0:45:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, passing a law.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:22.21,0:45:25.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, committing a crime is already against the law.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:28.21,0:45:29.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It's already against the law.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:31.21,0:45:32.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, next thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:32.71,0:45:33.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Next thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:33.71,0:45:36.51,Default,,0,0,0,,A rate of happiness, as you can see.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:37.01,0:45:45.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, so the, the level of consciousness, uh, here, it runs up to a thousand.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:45.76,0:45:49.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Enlightenment cali, it calibrates 700 and over.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:49.76,0:45:51.42,Default,,0,0,0,,700 and over.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:51.92,0:45:56.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, mental peace calibrates 600 and over.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:56.80,0:45:59.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Joy is at 570.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:00.80,0:46:04.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Reason is the consciousness level of four hundreds.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:04.30,0:46:19.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So our, uh, world, uh, celebrates the intellect, the capacity for reason and intelligence, ca, capacity to see the logic and the proof of things.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:20.07,0:46:26.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And very often people want to apply reason to things that are not really, uh, within the realm of reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:27.09,0:46:30.59,Default,,0,0,0,,They're within the realm of the heart and not of the intellect.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:31.09,0:46:31.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:32.55,0:46:34.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Willingness is 310.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:34.05,0:46:35.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Calibrates 310.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:36.15,0:46:37.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, neutrality.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:38.15,0:46:39.65,Default,,0,0,0,,That's, life is okay if it goes this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:40.15,0:46:42.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It's, it's okay if it goes that, that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:43.15,0:46:46.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So, uh, that's the best way to be about politics, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:49.44,0:46:50.44,Default,,0,0,0,,If they win, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:50.94,0:46:51.94,Default,,0,0,0,,If they win, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:52.44,0:46:53.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You sleep better, anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:55.44,0:46:58.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Courage is consciousness level 200 and over.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:59.78,0:47:00.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:00.78,0:47:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Now we get to the levels below 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:03.28,0:47:08.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the positive levels calibrate 200 and over.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:08.57,0:47:12.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And as you get less than 200, you get down to.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:12.90,0:47:15.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Pride calibrates at 175.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:16.40,0:47:18.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Pride goeth before a fall, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:19.42,0:47:23.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Percent of people who calibrate there is about 22.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:24.42,0:47:28.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So about a quarter of the population is operating off pride.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:29.84,0:47:33.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, a smaller percentage live in the world of anger.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:33.34,0:47:35.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, they're always angry about something.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:36.46,0:47:37.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Calibrate level 150.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:38.46,0:47:41.96,Default,,0,0,0,,About 12% of the population is angry all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:42.46,0:47:43.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Angry all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:44.57,0:47:46.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So you want to avoid them on the road.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:50.07,0:47:52.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You want to avoid them on the road.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:52.57,0:47:55.57,Default,,0,0,0,,They're mad all the time about everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:56.07,0:48:00.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, then we hit desire at 125.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:00.88,0:48:03.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Is a, is really sort of a cravingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:03.88,0:48:06.38,Default,,0,0,0,,It's, you're constantly wanting something.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:06.88,0:48:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Constantly craving and wanting.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:09.38,0:48:11.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, so that's desire.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:12.11,0:48:16.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Consciousness level below desire is one of fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:16.94,0:48:21.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So about 10% of the population live in the world of fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:21.94,0:48:23.94,Default,,0,0,0,,They're afraid of everything all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:24.69,0:48:29.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, and their whole life is based on defending themselves against their fears.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:30.19,0:48:34.92,Default,,0,0,0,,75, consciousness level 75 is grief.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:36.00,0:48:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,These people are sad about something all the time, sad.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:39.50,0:48:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And if they can't think of anything to be sad about, they'll remember something sad in the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:44.50,0:48:48.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So they're sort of hooked into, uh, sadness.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:48.65,0:48:52.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Um, less than that is apathy.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:52.65,0:48:55.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Apathy, it, what's the use?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:55.65,0:48:57.15,Default,,0,0,0,,It's, it's useless.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:57.65,0:49:02.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And then a certain percentage of the people, uh, live in the world of hatred all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:03.32,0:49:05.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And at the bottom of the,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:05.32,0:49:08.92,Default,,0,0,0,,the bottom of the list, the calibration level 30,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:09.42,0:49:12.92,Default,,0,0,0,,are the people who live in, uh, guilt all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:13.42,0:49:19.53,Default,,0,0,0,,4% of the people live all the time feeling guilty about something.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:20.03,0:49:20.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:21.03,0:49:22.36,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:23.15,0:49:25.76,Default,,0,0,0,,That's, uh, uh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:26.26,0:49:29.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So the calibrated levels of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:29.55,0:49:36.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been asked to do them on many, many famous, uh, spiritual teachers and gurus throughout history.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:36.55,0:49:37.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And, uh,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:38.09,0:49:41.09,Default,,0,0,0,,so we made a, a list of them for ready reference.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:41.59,0:49:49.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And periodically, in fact, that's the big, the biggest, uh, problem we get coming in the internet,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:49.98,0:49:54.48,Default,,0,0,0,,is, uh, some of you will find a spiritual teacher who's not on the list
Dialogue: 0,0:49:54.98,0:50:00.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and ask us to corroborate whether that person, you know, is, is over 200 or not,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:00.98,0:50:03.48,Default,,0,0,0,,or whether, what their level of consciousness is.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:04.07,0:50:07.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Because, uh, there, there are a number of fake gurus out, uh,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:08.57,0:50:13.07,Default,,0,0,0,,out there, and, and a lot of them are into making money in fake, fake gurus.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.57,0:50:21.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So we have, uh, for reference then, uh, the reference level of spiritual teachers.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:21.71,0:50:25.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And you'll find it's quite interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:26.15,0:50:39.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, Bodhidharma, Black Elk, uh, John Calvin, Confucius, uh, the current Dalai Lama.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:40.61,0:50:47.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Um, here we have, so if you haven't looked it up in the book, if you're interested in,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:48.23,0:50:52.73,Default,,0,0,0,,you can see Mahatma Gandhi, Mahatma Gandhi who stood off the British Empire.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:53.23,0:50:57.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So as you see, as the calibrated level goes up, the power goes up.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:58.50,0:51:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The power goes up to the point where Mahatma Gandhi, standing alone, half naked, uh, calibrating at 760,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:09.50,0:51:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,beat back the entire British Empire.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:12.00,0:51:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Without firing a shot.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:15.03,0:51:20.98,Default,,0,0,0,,How could that skinny little guy stand off the power of the British Empire?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:21.48,0:51:25.34,Default,,0,0,0,,The British Empire was the greatest power the world had ever seen.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:25.84,0:51:32.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And Mahatma Gandhi knocked them on their tail because he calibrated at 760.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:32.51,0:51:36.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Now we have all the other great teachers here.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:36.80,0:51:42.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, and if there's any you need to know, uh, if they're on the list,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:42.50,0:51:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,if there's anybody that you want to know and is not on there, uh, we'll be glad to do them right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:49.50,0:51:50.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:51.42,0:51:55.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And here we have Mutkananda, people that are well known.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:56.34,0:51:57.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, Dogen.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:58.57,0:52:00.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, we'll go on to the next.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:00.57,0:52:02.11,Default,,0,0,0,,St. John of the Cross.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:02.61,0:52:07.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Famous spiritual leaders from past life.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:07.88,0:52:09.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And I like Huang Po.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:10.92,0:52:12.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Huang Po was at 960.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:12.92,0:52:13.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:14.34,0:52:14.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:14.84,0:52:18.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So here we have all the famous popes.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:18.90,0:52:24.78,Default,,0,0,0,,All the famous, uh, spiritual teachers of the past and the present.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:25.28,0:52:27.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Very interesting thing to know.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:28.48,0:52:28.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:29.57,0:52:31.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And here's Master Suzuki.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:31.57,0:52:32.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:32.57,0:52:34.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And who else is up there we know?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:34.57,0:52:36.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we know all of them, actually.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:36.57,0:52:42.07,Default,,0,0,0,,We, anybody who is a student of spiritual reality is probably familiar with almost all these names.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:42.57,0:52:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,At least you've run across them.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:44.07,0:52:47.57,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's very nice to have a point of reference.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:48.07,0:52:52.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, point of reference so you know what you're talking about.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:52.88,0:52:54.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:55.38,0:52:56.38,Default,,0,0,0,,What's next?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:58.32,0:52:58.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:59.32,0:53:01.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Avatars and great spiritual teachers.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:01.82,0:53:02.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:03.42,0:53:04.92,Default,,0,0,0,,We did the greatest teachers of all time.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:05.42,0:53:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:06.65,0:53:08.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus Christ calibrates at a thousand.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:09.15,0:53:10.65,Default,,0,0,0,,The Buddha at a thousand.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:11.28,0:53:12.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Krishna, one thousand.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:13.28,0:53:15.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Zoroaster, a thousand.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:15.28,0:53:19.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The Christian apostles are almost all at a thousand.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:20.19,0:53:24.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The name of God is Om 975.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:24.61,0:53:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,John the Baptist, Moses, Abraham, Saint Paul, Muhammad at the time of, he dictated the Koran.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:35.94,0:53:39.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And Muhammad after age 38 changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:40.09,0:53:44.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So, that's why when we talk about the Koran, it's important to know.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:45.48,0:53:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Muhammad, at the time he dictated the Koran.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:49.46,0:53:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,With 700.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:52.26,0:53:54.76,Default,,0,0,0,,He had temporal lobe epilepsy.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:56.09,0:53:59.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And after the age of 38, he suddenly went to 130.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:00.09,0:54:05.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So, that was one of the spiritual disasters of mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:06.28,0:54:10.78,Default,,0,0,0,,It happened to a number of other great teachers too that they crashed later in life.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:11.28,0:54:12.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, for some reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:13.28,0:54:16.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So, it's necessary to know the writings of some great teachers.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:17.28,0:54:18.92,Default,,0,0,0,,At what age was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:19.42,0:54:20.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And what year was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:20.92,0:54:24.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you'll see over time that it suddenly changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:24.92,0:54:26.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:27.30,0:54:28.80,Default,,0,0,0,,What else have we got?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:31.44,0:54:34.94,Default,,0,0,0,,The great spiritual writings. Great spiritual writings.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:35.44,0:54:38.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Course in Miracles, calibrated 550.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:39.44,0:54:41.94,Default,,0,0,0,,How many people here have done the Course in Miracles?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:42.44,0:54:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,A lot of people, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:44.26,0:54:46.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Yep.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:47.01,0:54:49.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Course in Miracles is fun to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:50.65,0:54:53.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Those of you who haven't done the Course in Miracles,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:53.82,0:54:55.82,Default,,0,0,0,,you better do the Course in Miracles.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:03.09,0:55:06.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The Course in Miracles is really fun to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:07.19,0:55:11.69,Default,,0,0,0,,You get one lesson, one sentence, one sentence a day.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:12.19,0:55:18.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And anybody can handle one sentence a day for a year.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:18.84,0:55:25.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you don't have to spend all day poring over very learned, complicated texts.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:26.26,0:55:31.76,Default,,0,0,0,,All you need is one simple sentence a day.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:32.26,0:55:33.76,Default,,0,0,0,,One simple sentence a day.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:34.26,0:55:39.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I want you all to promise to do the Course in Miracles.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:40.13,0:55:42.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Then do the Course in Miracles.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:43.32,0:55:45.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Promise me.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:45.61,0:55:49.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It's great fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:50.03,0:55:51.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It's great fun to do the Course in Miracles.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:52.03,0:55:58.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And interestingly enough, as you do the Course in Miracles,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:58.57,0:56:00.57,Default,,0,0,0,,the miraculous begins to occur.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:01.78,0:56:04.78,Default,,0,0,0,,People will say, I've never experienced a miracle or seen one.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:05.28,0:56:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, do the Course in Miracles.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:06.96,0:56:10.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And then come back to me a year from now and tell me about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:12.46,0:56:15.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody's ever done the Course in Miracles who has not experienced a miracle.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:16.46,0:56:19.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you could be the first one, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:25.34,0:56:28.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Could be God really thinks you are a creep.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:30.92,0:56:32.42,Default,,0,0,0,,You suspect you're a creep and God agreed.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:32.92,0:56:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:36.96,0:56:38.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I always like that joke.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:38.96,0:56:40.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I've told it many times, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:40.46,0:56:41.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The guy, everything happens to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:42.96,0:56:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, his wife leaves him.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:44.96,0:56:45.96,Default,,0,0,0,,He gets sick.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:45.96,0:56:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,He loses his job.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:47.96,0:56:49.96,Default,,0,0,0,,He gets a case of the crud and it won't heal up.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:52.96,0:56:54.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And he goes out on the sidewalk.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:54.46,0:56:57.73,Default,,0,0,0,,He says, God, why me, God?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:57.73,0:56:58.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Why me?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:58.73,0:57:01.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And the voice comes out of the heavens and says, I don't know, Rudolph.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:01.23,0:57:03.23,Default,,0,0,0,,There's just something about you that pisses me off.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:07.76,0:57:09.26,Default,,0,0,0,,That's such a funny joke.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:11.50,0:57:18.59,Default,,0,0,0,,These are the great spiritual writings.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:18.59,0:57:26.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody who's been into spirituality are familiar with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:26.59,0:57:31.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The great, the Book of Kells, we went to Ireland.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:31.59,0:57:33.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Was it Ireland or Scotland?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:33.59,0:57:34.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Ireland, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:34.59,0:57:37.59,Default,,0,0,0,,To the university there to see the Book of Kells.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:37.59,0:57:41.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And then the Book of Mormon and all.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:41.59,0:57:43.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So, a person who is spiritual.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:44.09,0:57:50.71,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're spiritually interested, we'll get a lot out of looking at all these things.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:50.71,0:57:58.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And which Bible, you say the Bible.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:58.28,0:58:06.69,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll notice the Lamsa translation of the Bible calibrates much higher than the King James Version.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:06.69,0:58:11.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So, if you're interested in the highest truth, try to get that translation.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:11.88,0:58:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, and then here's the Talmud and the Torah, the Tibetan Book of the Dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:16.88,0:58:18.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And the Bible.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:18.86,0:58:25.05,Default,,0,0,0,,The Vedas, the Vedanta, and the Yoga Sutras of Patanjali.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:25.05,0:58:26.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:26.05,0:58:33.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So, this list covers a great many of the world's most famous spiritual writings.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:33.34,0:58:39.86,Default,,0,0,0,,We wanted to write, you know, say something about love.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:39.86,0:58:45.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Love is consciousness level 500 and over.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:45.03,0:58:49.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And we saw that 500 was the level of the bagpipes.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:49.03,0:58:50.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that interesting?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:50.03,0:58:50.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:51.03,0:58:57.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the sound of the bagpipes is the sound of the heart of mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:57.03,0:59:04.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason everybody cries when they hear the bagpipes coming is because it's the sound,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:04.19,0:59:08.42,Default,,0,0,0,,the energy field of the heart of mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:08.42,0:59:19.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And so, classically, the people who have been in the service especially will have the bagpipes at their funeral.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:19.82,0:59:20.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:20.82,0:59:24.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it expresses that kind of love.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:24.34,0:59:27.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Love consciousness level 500.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:27.34,0:59:30.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It starts out as feeling warmth.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:30.34,0:59:34.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Warmth towards other people.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:34.59,0:59:38.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It expresses appreciation.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:38.86,0:59:43.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I know somebody who is very demanding and disliked as a consequence.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:43.86,0:59:48.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And she never expresses appreciation for anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:48.17,0:59:51.17,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, would you mind when you go to town getting me 52 pounds of potatoes?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:51.17,0:59:53.17,Default,,0,0,0,,52 pounds of potatoes and hauling them home.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:53.17,0:59:57.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And then when you get them home, she doesn't even say, gee, thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:57.17,1:00:03.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Consequently, as time goes on, people are less and less willing to do things for her.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:03.17,1:00:07.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So, a simple thank you makes a tremendous difference.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:07.50,1:00:10.59,Default,,0,0,0,,People say, well, that's just being polite.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:10.59,1:00:13.59,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it's not just being polite.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:13.59,1:00:18.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It's acknowledging the worth of other human beings in your world.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:18.82,1:00:20.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you appreciate and you give thanks.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:20.82,1:00:25.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Love level 500 and over.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:25.07,1:00:28.07,Default,,0,0,0,,It shows appreciation.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:28.07,1:00:30.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Love is supportive.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:30.07,1:00:33.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, mutual support.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:33.07,1:00:35.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Love is also forgiving.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:35.55,1:00:39.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So, if the world makes a mistake, you're willing to forgive it.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:39.57,1:00:44.42,Default,,0,0,0,,If people make a mistake, you're willing to forgive them.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:44.42,1:00:50.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the willingness to forgive marks a truly spiritual person.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:50.42,1:00:52.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The willingness to forgive.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:52.42,1:00:55.42,Default,,0,0,0,,To let bygones be bygones.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:55.42,1:01:00.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And I think the 12-step group emphasizes the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:00.42,1:01:04.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Live one day at a time and let bygones be bygones.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:04.42,1:01:10.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Somebody did you a bad term, the people in the group will tell you, well, that was yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:10.42,1:01:13.42,Default,,0,0,0,,That was yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:13.42,1:01:18.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Love is also inclusive.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:18.05,1:01:20.05,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not exclusive.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:20.05,1:01:23.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It's also affectionate.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:23.11,1:01:28.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And it has to do with being cordial and gracious.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:28.46,1:01:30.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And gracious.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:30.46,1:01:40.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So, to be cordial and gracious and acknowledge other people and the gift of their presence.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:40.19,1:01:45.19,Default,,0,0,0,,When you say thank you, people think that's just manners.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:45.19,1:01:47.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not just manners.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:47.19,1:01:52.26,Default,,0,0,0,,When you say thank you, you totally change the energy field.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:52.26,1:01:54.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You totally change the energy field.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:54.26,1:01:56.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You become uplifting.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:56.26,1:02:03.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So, people above 200 are supporting all of life.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:03.09,1:02:06.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And below 200, they are dragging down on it.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:06.09,1:02:13.65,Default,,0,0,0,,So, when you're uplifting, you are adding to the energy field of all of life.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:13.65,1:02:17.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And especially of human life.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:17.11,1:02:20.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Love is also heartfelt.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:20.11,1:02:23.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It's called heartfelt and nurturing.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:23.11,1:02:25.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Love is also understanding.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:25.42,1:02:28.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It's protective.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:28.65,1:02:31.75,Default,,0,0,0,,It's dedicated to goodness.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:31.75,1:02:33.75,Default,,0,0,0,,It's dedicated to purity.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:33.75,1:02:36.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It's dedicated to giving to others.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:36.90,1:02:40.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Love is generous.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:40.36,1:02:43.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Love is also capable of sharing.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:43.42,1:02:45.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It's also nonlinear.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:45.86,1:02:47.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It's holistic.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:47.86,1:02:49.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It arises from the heart.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:49.86,1:02:56.07,Default,,0,0,0,,In lovingness, we join with other.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:56.07,1:02:58.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And we diffuse that love.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:58.07,1:03:01.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And set it up around us.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:01.07,1:03:04.07,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a way of being aligned.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:04.07,1:03:06.07,Default,,0,0,0,,It's also humbling.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:06.07,1:03:10.40,Default,,0,0,0,,When it's humble and not prideful in lovingness.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:10.40,1:03:12.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And we express our gratitude.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:12.46,1:03:15.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And when we do that, there's completion.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:15.46,1:03:20.50,Default,,0,0,0,,When you express your gratitude and say thank you, that completes the transaction.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:20.50,1:03:26.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the failure to say thank you means rejecting the other person instead of accepting them.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:26.69,1:03:30.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Their donation of love.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:30.84,1:03:35.07,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a certain sweetness to love.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:35.07,1:03:40.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Love has a certain capacity to attract affection.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:40.57,1:03:41.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:41.57,1:03:46.01,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:46.01,1:03:47.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh!
Dialogue: 0,1:03:47.01,1:03:50.55,Default,,0,0,0,,How'd he get in there?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:53.76,1:03:55.76,Default,,0,0,0,,There's the sheep in wolf's clothing.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:55.76,1:03:58.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:58.09,1:04:00.09,Default,,0,0,0,,When do we take a break?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:00.09,1:04:03.42,Default,,0,0,0,,In about three minutes.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:03.42,1:04:04.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:04.42,1:04:07.07,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:07.07,1:04:10.38,Default,,0,0,0,,This is important to know in today's world.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:10.38,1:04:15.01,Default,,0,0,0,,We haven't gotten around to today's world yet.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:15.01,1:04:17.01,Default,,0,0,0,,This is important to know.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:17.01,1:04:30.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Because one of the ways negativity tends to prevail, how it gets such a hold in life,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:30.40,1:04:36.53,Default,,0,0,0,,is because it misrepresents itself as sheep.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:36.53,1:04:37.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:37.84,1:04:38.84,Default,,0,0,0,,The sheep.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:38.84,1:04:39.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't bother about us.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:39.84,1:04:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,We're just a happy religion.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:41.84,1:04:42.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, right.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:43.84,1:04:45.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Until you hear the gunfire.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:49.84,1:04:51.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for all those love fellows.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:56.34,1:04:59.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So, this is our friend.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:59.86,1:05:01.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is a good one to keep in mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:01.86,1:05:04.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Because when we get to talking about today's world,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:04.86,1:05:08.44,Default,,0,0,0,,we are going to be indirectly in love.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:09.44,1:05:14.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Unconsciously referring to situations that today prevail.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:14.44,1:05:16.78,Default,,0,0,0,,We're just innocent do-gooders.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:16.78,1:05:17.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:17.78,1:05:18.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:18.78,1:05:22.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Put away the machine guns and I can believe you even better.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:23.78,1:05:29.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, what do we do now?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:29.98,1:05:30.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Turn me on?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:30.98,1:05:36.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You turn me on, sweetheart.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:36.94,1:05:44.23,Default,,0,0,0,,You got to put a dime in the corner of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:44.23,1:05:46.42,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:46.42,1:05:48.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I have to do this announcement.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:48.42,1:05:49.42,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:49.42,1:05:50.42,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to take a quick break.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:50.42,1:05:52.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And we'll see you back here in about 15 minutes.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:53.42,1:06:47.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:47.94,1:06:52.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And now, I don't know what happens next, but they'll let us know.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:52.98,1:06:55.82,Default,,0,0,0,,What do we do next, sweetheart?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:55.82,1:06:59.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Continue the lecture?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:59.46,1:07:02.61,Default,,0,0,0,,She's my living, breathing teleprompter.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:05.15,1:07:07.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Beats Obama's hands down.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:11.94,1:07:14.98,Default,,0,0,0,,She knows what's going on all the time.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:14.98,1:07:20.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Spiritual survival in today's world.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:20.11,1:07:21.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:21.11,1:07:25.65,Default,,0,0,0,,The realities of the levels of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:25.65,1:07:30.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Reality is a subjective mental presumption.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:30.65,1:07:32.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:32.26,1:07:35.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Reality is a presumption.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:35.78,1:07:39.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You ever think of that?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:39.78,1:07:42.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You presume that what you're seeing is real.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:43.78,1:07:45.78,Default,,0,0,0,,But you could be a lunatic.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:46.78,1:07:51.67,Default,,0,0,0,,In which case, nothing that you're looking at is real.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:51.67,1:07:54.42,Default,,0,0,0,,You made it all up.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:54.42,1:07:58.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, is reality a subjective mental presumption?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:58.42,1:07:59.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:59.82,1:08:02.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:02.05,1:08:03.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:03.05,1:08:06.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Linear versus nonlinear.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:06.84,1:08:11.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Linear versus nonlinear.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:11.15,1:08:13.69,Default,,0,0,0,,What does that mean?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:13.69,1:08:17.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Logical or not logical?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:17.05,1:08:23.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you notice the field of consciousness is neither logical nor is it nonlogical.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:23.27,1:08:28.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It just does not address the problem at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:28.68,1:08:31.68,Default,,0,0,0,,One just experiences what you experience.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:31.68,1:08:35.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And making a conclusion about it requires thinkingness.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:36.68,1:08:42.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Consciousness itself is not the same as thinkingness.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:42.81,1:08:44.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Thinkingness is something else again.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:45.17,1:08:52.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So reality is a subjective mental presumption.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:52.61,1:08:57.61,Default,,0,0,0,,We presume that what we see is what is, what really is.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:57.61,1:09:02.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And reality is one thing, truth is another.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:02.84,1:09:08.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Existentially, is the me real?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:09.22,1:09:15.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You presume you're real, but are you?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:15.59,1:09:18.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You never worried about that before.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:18.59,1:09:23.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh good, now there's something new to worry about.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:23.06,1:09:28.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Is the me just my imagination?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:28.98,1:09:33.98,Default,,0,0,0,,There are levels of consciousness where that really becomes a problem.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:33.98,1:09:39.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Is there actually a me or is that just some kind of a delusion?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:39.34,1:09:41.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And what is this I?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:41.50,1:09:44.50,Default,,0,0,0,,What is this I, everything that I call I?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:44.50,1:09:50.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do you call it me or I in the first place?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:50.46,1:09:55.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, is the I that which witnesses the world?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:55.86,1:10:01.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Is the I that which experiences the world?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:01.92,1:10:07.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Is the I that which makes choices?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:07.22,1:10:11.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Has to do with the human will and volition?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:11.48,1:10:16.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Then there's the I as a social personhood.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:16.60,1:10:19.09,Default,,0,0,0,,People say you are.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:19.09,1:10:20.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You are what?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:20.09,1:10:23.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Then there is I as my feelings.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:23.63,1:10:25.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Am I my feelings?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:25.65,1:10:28.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Or am I my thoughts?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:28.05,1:10:32.61,Default,,0,0,0,,How do I know that I even am?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:36.84,1:10:38.84,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you know that you are?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:38.84,1:10:42.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I know I am because I think and because I feel.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:42.84,1:10:47.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And because other people seem to think that I am.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:47.35,1:10:50.42,Default,,0,0,0,,That's reassuring.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:50.42,1:10:51.93,Default,,0,0,0,,What can a Roman people say?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:51.93,1:10:52.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Roman people say hello.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:52.93,1:10:55.93,Default,,0,0,0,,You say, oh boy.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:55.93,1:10:56.93,Default,,0,0,0,,What a relief.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:56.93,1:11:03.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I wasn't sure if I was or not.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:03.13,1:11:09.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Is the real self just a blank screen on which everything is reflected?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:09.82,1:11:17.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Is the real self the content or the context?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:17.84,1:11:19.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Descartes' proposition.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:19.84,1:11:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Is reality res interna, that is the way I experience things?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:26.96,1:11:29.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Or is it res externa?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:30.40,1:11:38.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Descartes differentiated between the world as I experience it versus the world as it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:38.89,1:11:44.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I may experience it as safe and it could be quite dangerous or vice versa.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:44.23,1:11:50.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So the self knows from one moment to the next.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:50.42,1:11:53.71,Default,,0,0,0,,The mind thinks.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:53.71,1:11:56.71,Default,,0,0,0,,So thinkingness is one thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:56.71,1:12:00.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Experiencing reality is another.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:00.02,1:12:02.02,Default,,0,0,0,,None of these things become very important
Dialogue: 0,1:12:02.02,1:12:05.44,Default,,0,0,0,,unless one is seeking enlightenment.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:05.44,1:12:07.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you seek enlightenment,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:07.44,1:12:13.60,Default,,0,0,0,,that you're letting go of many of the things that the world presumes are necessary.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:13.60,1:12:17.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And you let them go.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:17.47,1:12:23.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And one thing you let go of is the mind's thinking.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:23.10,1:12:26.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, if you can't think anymore,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:26.10,1:12:31.18,Default,,0,0,0,,you're only left with knowing.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:31.18,1:12:33.18,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you know without thinking?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:33.18,1:12:36.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you discover that you know without thinking all the time.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:36.18,1:12:39.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And that thinking is just added as a frill.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:43.26,1:12:46.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Thinking is a frill in an entertainment.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:48.26,1:12:50.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you get along without thinking?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:50.26,1:12:54.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I'm not going to think about anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:59.48,1:13:01.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess I should have thought.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:03.52,1:13:06.02,Default,,0,0,0,,There is a chair there.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:06.02,1:13:09.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I don't think about the chair.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:10.26,1:13:11.26,Default,,0,0,0,,But I know.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:11.26,1:13:13.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I know it's there.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:13.42,1:13:19.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So most of real knowingness goes on without thinkingness.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:19.60,1:13:21.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Thinkingness is something we add.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:21.60,1:13:24.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The human adds thinking.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:24.98,1:13:26.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The animal knows without thinking.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:26.98,1:13:31.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It knows its friend from foe.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:31.25,1:13:35.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The dog's hackles goes up if it's foe.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:35.78,1:13:38.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And its tail wags if it's friend.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:38.81,1:13:40.81,Default,,0,0,0,,So the dog doesn't have to think about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:40.81,1:13:45.89,Default,,0,0,0,,It just knows right off the bat who is the friend and who is the burglar.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:47.89,1:13:48.89,Default,,0,0,0,,A burglar.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:48.89,1:13:50.97,Default,,0,0,0,,That's such a funny term, a burglar.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:50.97,1:13:53.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't it funny?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:53.21,1:13:54.21,Default,,0,0,0,,What does a burglar do?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:54.21,1:13:55.21,Default,,0,0,0,,He burgles.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:01.34,1:14:05.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You can go to burglar school.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:05.46,1:14:08.93,Default,,0,0,0,,They do that in jail.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:08.93,1:14:16.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Prisons are really burglar schools in which they trade information
Dialogue: 0,1:14:16.06,1:14:18.06,Default,,0,0,0,,so they're better at it next time.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:18.06,1:14:22.36,Default,,0,0,0,,We saw a movie the other night about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:22.36,1:14:26.36,Default,,0,0,0,,A true case of a guy who really learned how to rob banks.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:26.36,1:14:28.36,Default,,0,0,0,,He had an excellent technique.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:28.36,1:14:31.36,Default,,0,0,0,,He was so good at it, he couldn't stop robbing banks.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:31.36,1:14:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,He robbed 12 in a row before the banking system became aware of its existence.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:38.88,1:14:41.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And they put a loaded money.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:41.88,1:14:47.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So in a bank teller, a guy holds a gun on her and says,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:47.88,1:14:48.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Give me your money.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:48.88,1:14:51.88,Default,,0,0,0,,She gives him this pack of bills and this pack of bills.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:51.88,1:14:54.88,Default,,0,0,0,,If he takes it out, it's got a timer on it.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:54.88,1:14:59.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And the timer is released and suddenly red ink squirts out all over.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:59.88,1:15:01.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And the cops have no problem finding him.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:01.88,1:15:07.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's best not to burglar banks.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:10.39,1:15:15.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Is reality, therefore, the essence or the appearance of a thing?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:15.18,1:15:18.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember Alice in Wonderland?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:18.77,1:15:21.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's all based on opinion.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:21.77,1:15:22.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Opinion.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:23.89,1:15:27.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Virtual reality of the media.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:27.40,1:15:31.75,Default,,0,0,0,,The world is a projection, an illusion.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:31.75,1:15:37.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The sense of reality occurs in one ten-thousandth of a second.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:37.88,1:15:44.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Within one ten-thousandth of a second, your mind is already aware
Dialogue: 0,1:15:44.42,1:15:48.89,Default,,0,0,0,,of whether it's an illusion or a reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:48.89,1:15:54.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So the mind by itself really is without a compass.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:54.42,1:15:56.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The mind has no capacity to tell truth from falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:56.51,1:16:07.53,Default,,0,0,0,,In the United States, 55% of the people are unable to differentiate reality from illusion.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:07.53,1:16:11.05,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you know about that?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:11.05,1:16:16.05,Default,,0,0,0,,55% can't tell reality from illusion?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:16.05,1:16:17.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that a fact?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:17.05,1:16:23.72,Default,,0,0,0,,55% of the people in the United States cannot tell reality from an illusion.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:23.72,1:16:26.30,Default,,0,0,0,,That explains the Daily News.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:29.30,1:16:34.47,Default,,0,0,0,,That explains the Daily News, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:34.47,1:16:39.14,Default,,0,0,0,,The mind does not have a compass to tell it.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:39.14,1:16:46.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, the system that we have evolved of how to tell truth from falsehood
Dialogue: 0,1:16:46.86,1:16:50.86,Default,,0,0,0,,is of very great pragmatic value.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:50.86,1:17:00.36,Default,,0,0,0,,In the United States, belief systems tend to get politicized.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:00.36,1:17:03.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Not only in the United States, but all around the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:03.36,1:17:05.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And...
Dialogue: 0,1:17:05.03,1:17:10.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Narcissism is the presumption that the way I look at it is correct
Dialogue: 0,1:17:10.68,1:17:15.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and the way you look at it is incorrect.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:15.31,1:17:16.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:16.31,1:17:21.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Indoctrination, we find, trumps reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:21.11,1:17:27.11,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, if we indoctrinate people, they lose the capacity to discern reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:27.11,1:17:32.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Indoctrination University is a book called Indoctrination
Dialogue: 0,1:17:32.25,1:17:36.38,Default,,0,0,0,,that documents how it's brought about.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:37.38,1:17:43.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, we could say all information is presumptive.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:43.34,1:17:49.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It's best to send your kids to Yavapai College.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:52.11,1:17:55.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Calibrates 440.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:55.47,1:17:58.47,Default,,0,0,0,,What did we calibrate Harvard Law at?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:58.47,1:18:00.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't we have Harvard Law on here?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:00.47,1:18:02.47,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the next slide?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:02.47,1:18:03.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:03.81,1:18:06.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:06.01,1:18:07.01,Default,,0,0,0,,No?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:07.01,1:18:10.02,Default,,0,0,0,,No?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:10.02,1:18:11.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:11.38,1:18:12.38,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:12.38,1:18:13.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go back to the last one.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:13.38,1:18:14.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Last one.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:14.38,1:18:23.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, reality is the essence of a thing versus its appearance.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:23.22,1:18:24.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:28.61,1:18:30.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Mind is without a compass.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:30.61,1:18:31.61,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:31.61,1:18:36.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So, therefore, the technique that we have evolved to discern truth from falsehood
Dialogue: 0,1:18:36.61,1:18:43.02,Default,,0,0,0,,is of very great pragmatic value.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:43.02,1:18:48.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know what happened to Harvard Law.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:48.30,1:18:49.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:49.30,1:18:50.35,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:50.35,1:18:51.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:51.35,1:18:52.35,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a 440.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:52.35,1:18:53.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Yavapai College.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:53.35,1:18:58.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Yavapai College calibrates at 440.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:58.26,1:19:02.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Harvard Law calibrates over 200.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:02.28,1:19:06.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Harvard Law calibrates over 200.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:06.81,1:19:12.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Harvard Law calibrates over 200.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:12.93,1:19:14.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Send your kids to Yavapai College.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:14.93,1:19:27.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Much to the shock and dismay of all the people I know who are lawyers,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:27.81,1:19:34.77,Default,,0,0,0,,that Harvard Law would someday calibrate so low it wasn't even thinkable.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:34.77,1:19:38.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And it has to do with Marxist indoctrination.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:38.77,1:19:43.38,Default,,0,0,0,,It has to do with social justice.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:43.38,1:19:45.56,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what did it.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:45.56,1:19:53.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The whole belief system of social justice is what brought Harvard Law down from what
Dialogue: 0,1:19:53.56,1:20:00.14,Default,,0,0,0,,once was the most respected institution, presidents, cabinet members, etc.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:00.14,1:20:01.14,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:01.14,1:20:06.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It's better to send your kids to Yavapai College than Harvard Law.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:06.57,1:20:12.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It's great to know that Yavapai College calibrates at 440.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:12.57,1:20:14.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I think that's tremendous.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:14.57,1:20:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:16.00,1:20:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So where is the next slide?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:18.00,1:20:21.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:21.09,1:20:29.23,Default,,0,0,0,,What you consider reality is really the product of a whole set of paradigms and presumptions.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:29.23,1:20:34.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Marx said religion is the opiate of the people.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:34.06,1:20:37.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Religion is the opiate of the people.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:37.81,1:20:40.82,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:40.82,1:20:47.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Alice in Wonderland is the internet and blogosphere.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:47.81,1:20:56.01,Default,,0,0,0,,The internet and blogosphere has totally dominated our sense of reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:56.01,1:21:09.80,Default,,0,0,0,,55% in America exhibit damaged capacity to discern reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:09.80,1:21:12.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, wow.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:12.47,1:21:18.68,Default,,0,0,0,,In the average police lineup to identify suspects,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:18.68,1:21:20.77,Default,,0,0,0,,the rate of...
Dialogue: 0,1:21:20.77,1:21:26.69,Default,,0,0,0,,error of identification is 50%.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:26.69,1:21:35.43,Default,,0,0,0,,So it gives us a certain idea then that about 50% of what we see on television
Dialogue: 0,1:21:35.43,1:21:43.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and our presumptions about it are not real or not reality or are not truthful.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:43.97,1:21:44.97,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:44.97,1:21:52.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So what we could say about 50% of what we see on television news is false, incorrect.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:52.14,1:21:54.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Incorrect.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:54.14,1:21:56.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Distorted.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:56.06,1:21:57.06,Default,,0,0,0,,50%.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:57.06,1:21:59.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that's a big input, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:59.06,1:22:00.14,Default,,0,0,0,,50% of what...
Dialogue: 0,1:22:00.14,1:22:05.14,Default,,0,0,0,,If 50% of the food you ate was bad, you'd be in bum shape.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:05.14,1:22:10.39,Default,,0,0,0,,So mental food, 50% is defective.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:10.39,1:22:11.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:11.97,1:22:16.61,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:16.61,1:22:21.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go on to the next slide.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:21.27,1:22:25.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Practical spirituality.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:25.48,1:22:30.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So our lecture is really not about how crazy the world is,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:30.73,1:22:35.89,Default,,0,0,0,,but practical spirituality.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:35.89,1:22:39.89,Default,,0,0,0,,What do we do about it if the world we see,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:39.89,1:22:49.23,Default,,0,0,0,,if the world as it is reported to us is 50% incorrect?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:49.23,1:22:51.23,Default,,0,0,0,,What is our salvation then?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:51.23,1:22:57.73,Default,,0,0,0,,What can we do to protect ourself from such deviance from truth?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:57.73,1:23:00.73,Default,,0,0,0,,One is to stay with holy company.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:00.73,1:23:01.73,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:01.73,1:23:02.86,Default,,0,0,0,,What does that mean?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:02.86,1:23:08.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It means that if people who are dedicated to spiritual truth,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:08.64,1:23:14.22,Default,,0,0,0,,who are spiritually oriented then,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:14.22,1:23:18.22,Default,,0,0,0,,themselves are constantly looking to verify the truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:18.22,1:23:25.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And when a whole group of people consistently verify certain teachings or teachers,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:25.61,1:23:28.97,Default,,0,0,0,,it's presumably safe.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:28.97,1:23:32.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Stay with holy company.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:32.25,1:23:38.64,Default,,0,0,0,,There's an energy field effect.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:38.64,1:23:40.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Alcoholics Anonymous is...
Dialogue: 0,1:23:40.64,1:23:51.63,Default,,0,0,0,,One of the best known levels of consciousness in actual daily practice.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:51.63,1:24:01.46,Default,,0,0,0,,AA calibrates over 450, 500, 499, 500.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:01.46,1:24:03.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Calibrates right at 500.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:03.59,1:24:04.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Yep.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:04.93,1:24:05.93,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:05.93,1:24:08.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So you stay with holy company.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:08.03,1:24:11.03,Default,,0,0,0,,People who have dedicated their lives to God,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:11.03,1:24:15.28,Default,,0,0,0,,to love,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:15.28,1:24:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,to transcend human error,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:17.28,1:24:20.60,Default,,0,0,0,,then are the people that you would look for.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:20.60,1:24:22.60,Default,,0,0,0,,A group such as this, for instance,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:22.60,1:24:24.64,Default,,0,0,0,,a group such as this,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:24.64,1:24:26.64,Default,,0,0,0,,is made up of spiritual seekers.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:26.64,1:24:28.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Spiritual seekers.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:28.64,1:24:31.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Most of the people here have studied with a number of teachers,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:31.64,1:24:32.64,Default,,0,0,0,,read a lot of books,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:32.64,1:24:35.89,Default,,0,0,0,,traveled and met,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:35.89,1:24:40.34,Default,,0,0,0,,been in various ashrams and various religions.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:40.34,1:24:42.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I myself have been all over the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:42.34,1:24:51.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Susan and I visited the great places of worship here and in Europe, etc.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:51.88,1:24:55.51,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:55.51,1:24:57.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Stay with holy company.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:57.51,1:25:01.96,Default,,0,0,0,,There is an energy in the field itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:01.96,1:25:11.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The relapse experience of AA is when one violates certain basic spiritual principles.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:11.42,1:25:18.77,Default,,0,0,0,,A very interesting TV series is The Band of Brothers.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:18.77,1:25:28.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Which reflects the bonding that goes on between men during war.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:28.10,1:25:37.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Cultural paradigms of reality tend to alter how we see and feel and experience and remember things.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:37.77,1:25:41.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course the karmic influences,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:41.01,1:25:45.01,Default,,0,0,0,,which are not familiar to Western society,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:45.01,1:25:50.10,Default,,0,0,0,,are presumed to be of extreme importance.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:50.10,1:25:54.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Then there's spirituality versus religious.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:54.64,1:25:58.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Religious is one thing, spiritual is another.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:58.73,1:26:07.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Paradoxically, a religion can become a source of evil, actually.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:07.47,1:26:17.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Some religions are taken over by forces that are then using them for other purposes than what they originated.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:17.64,1:26:20.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Spiritual, then, stays with truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:20.85,1:26:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And religious can be influenced.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:24.96,1:26:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,In today's world, you see that very markedly.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:30.96,1:26:33.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And what's the next one?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:33.40,1:26:38.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Practical spirituality.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:38.77,1:26:45.10,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, how do you survive in a world where at least 50% of what you see in here is fallacious?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:45.10,1:26:48.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Or twisted, anyway.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:48.10,1:26:51.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So you find a primary teacher.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:51.22,1:26:52.22,Default,,0,0,0,,One that you can...
Dialogue: 0,1:26:52.22,1:27:00.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Whose capacity to discern truth from falsehood can be verified.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:00.22,1:27:05.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And this primary teacher puts principles above personalities.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:05.57,1:27:13.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Personalities are interesting, but it's basic provable principles.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:13.18,1:27:19.18,Default,,0,0,0,,We have that chart of authenticated teachers, which we showed you before.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:19.18,1:27:23.69,Default,,0,0,0,,It's best to avoid new ageism.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:23.69,1:27:31.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The popularity comes and goes of new age gurus and popular teachings.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:31.69,1:27:36.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Some of which take you far afield.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:36.10,1:27:43.42,Default,,0,0,0,,What appeals to lots of people are things that are exotic.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:43.42,1:27:51.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, shave your head and walk around barefoot and half-naked and just live on bananas or something.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:51.57,1:27:55.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Join an ashram and fast around the clock for seven days.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:55.57,1:28:05.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I always say, fasting as a spiritual principle heals itself in the end.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:05.22,1:28:13.65,Default,,0,0,0,,If you fast long enough, you don't have any further problems in life.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:13.65,1:28:21.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I once tried to see how long you could go without eating.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:21.52,1:28:24.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I forget, I think after three weeks or a month I gave up.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:24.77,1:28:28.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't remember why I ate something.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:28.73,1:28:31.73,Default,,0,0,0,,But it was either that or croaks.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:31.73,1:28:32.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess my mind decided...
Dialogue: 0,1:28:32.73,1:28:40.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It's best to avoid, you know, channeled entities.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:40.97,1:28:47.14,Default,,0,0,0,,People who are channeled, some of them calibrate over 200.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:47.14,1:28:49.14,Default,,0,0,0,,A lot of them do not.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:49.14,1:28:56.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And I would not pick a channeled entity as my guru, as my teacher.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:56.30,1:29:02.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And sometimes they are useful and practical.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:02.68,1:29:04.81,Default,,0,0,0,,But you have to really test them out.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:04.81,1:29:07.81,Default,,0,0,0,,To see whether or not that's true.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:07.81,1:29:13.06,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, you channel Master Buha from Waggi Waggi Land.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:13.06,1:29:15.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And he once lived 2,000 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:17.31,1:29:22.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It's anybody's guess whether it's going to be of practical use to you or not.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:22.31,1:29:26.31,Default,,0,0,0,,So avoid the attraction of that which is exotic.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:26.31,1:29:33.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And channeled, as I said, channeled entities are buyer beware.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:33.69,1:29:38.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And avoid self-styled masters.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:38.11,1:29:42.11,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, some guy used to come around and he called himself Master so-and-so.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:42.11,1:29:45.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Why does he call himself Master or something, rather?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:45.11,1:29:51.76,Default,,0,0,0,,He didn't calibrate over too impressive, much less Master, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:51.76,1:29:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I am Master so-and-so.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:53.76,1:29:57.61,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:57.61,1:30:05.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Master is a title that society gives to those who have proven themselves to actually be a Master.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:05.86,1:30:09.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Master over periods of time.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:09.69,1:30:12.69,Default,,0,0,0,,You ask him, when did you become a Master?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:12.69,1:30:17.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, last Tuesday.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:17.78,1:30:20.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Last Tuesday.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:20.27,1:30:22.68,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:22.68,1:30:30.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So the way that we have all traveled of practical spirituality is by study.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:30.01,1:30:34.19,Default,,0,0,0,,We all study the great teachers of time.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:34.19,1:30:37.19,Default,,0,0,0,,We study the holy books.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:37.42,1:30:42.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So we use our intellect to study.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:42.61,1:30:46.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And then we contemplate it and meditate.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:46.68,1:30:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So you may read one sentence and spend a week contemplating that one sentence.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:53.00,1:30:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You just hold that in mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:55.00,1:31:01.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And I ask God, what does that mean, what I just thought, what I just said in my mind?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:01.10,1:31:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,What does that mean?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:03.44,1:31:06.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And I turn the problem over to God.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:06.44,1:31:15.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And in a non-verbal revelation, it suddenly becomes starkly obvious.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:15.89,1:31:18.89,Default,,0,0,0,,So you balance faith and reason.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:18.89,1:31:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't be foolish and stupid, and neither can you can't just trust reason.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:27.00,1:31:34.93,Default,,0,0,0,,It's one thing to become a spiritual goal, and it's another to know about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:34.93,1:31:38.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Many people who speak know about it,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:38.98,1:31:44.52,Default,,0,0,0,,but as yet have not become it.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:44.52,1:31:47.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Avoid all hatred doctrines.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:47.68,1:31:55.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Right now, the hatred seems to be quite popular in the media.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:55.02,1:32:00.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Hate groups seem to be specialized, in politics especially.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:00.18,1:32:05.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Hatred seems to prevail as a current fashionable style.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:12.23,1:32:13.23,Default,,0,0,0,,How can you tell
Dialogue: 0,1:32:13.23,1:32:15.23,Default,,0,0,0,,when a politician is lying?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:15.23,1:32:17.97,Default,,0,0,0,,When you see his lips moving.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:32.77,1:32:34.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh God, that is so funny.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:37.86,1:32:39.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And yet if you test it with the arm,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:39.86,1:32:54.25,Default,,0,0,0,,if you test it with the arm, you'll find that very often your intuition is correct.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:54.25,1:32:57.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Very often your intuition is correct.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:57.47,1:32:58.94,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:58.94,1:33:01.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Through study, through contemplation, through meditation,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:01.94,1:33:04.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I ask God to lead me to the truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:04.94,1:33:06.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And
Dialogue: 0,1:33:06.30,1:33:08.39,Default,,0,0,0,,by faith in the process,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:08.39,1:33:11.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and faith in God and a spiritual teacher.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:11.39,1:33:16.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, in today's world we can calibrate a spiritual teacher.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:16.68,1:33:17.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:17.68,1:33:20.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And so therefore we calibrate them and see.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:20.68,1:33:23.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Recently we did a whole bunch of them.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:23.72,1:33:30.77,Default,,0,0,0,,A couple of students and myself calibrated a whole bunch of well-known teachers over great periods of time.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:30.77,1:33:34.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And actually they all came out pretty well, actually.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:34.81,1:33:40.81,Default,,0,0,0,,So their reputation was pretty aligned with truth, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:40.81,1:33:44.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Spiritual ego meaning is holier than thou.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:44.84,1:33:47.84,Default,,0,0,0,,To believe that you're holier than other people.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:47.84,1:33:50.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Or that you're more advanced or you're more enlightened.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:50.84,1:33:54.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And as I say, if you're enlightened, you wouldn't know it anyway.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:57.93,1:34:01.13,Default,,0,0,0,,That's something that other people say about you.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:01.13,1:34:04.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Many things inspire us.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:04.13,1:34:06.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Beautiful music.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:06.13,1:34:08.13,Default,,0,0,0,,The giant cathedrals.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:08.13,1:34:09.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Beauty.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:09.28,1:34:13.96,Default,,0,0,0,,As you spiritually evolve, you find you're more and more attracted by beauty.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:13.96,1:34:18.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And you begin to see the beauty of all that exists.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:18.02,1:34:21.14,Default,,0,0,0,,The inspiration of great music.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:21.14,1:34:23.14,Default,,0,0,0,,The great cathedrals of the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:23.14,1:34:27.31,Default,,0,0,0,,See how many people here have visited the great cathedrals of the world?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:27.31,1:34:28.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:28.31,1:34:29.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Quite a few, yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:29.31,1:34:35.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And right near Cottonwood here now there's a new beautiful cathedral.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:35.27,1:34:37.27,Default,,0,0,0,,A new beautiful church.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:37.27,1:34:40.27,Default,,0,0,0,,With an incredible stained glass window.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:40.27,1:34:42.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't expect anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:42.50,1:34:47.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought out of curiosity I pulled over and we went inside to see what it looked like.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:47.75,1:34:50.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And wow, here was a whole window.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:50.93,1:34:55.93,Default,,0,0,0,,A stained glass window that was just incredible.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:55.93,1:34:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And some of the great cathedrals of the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:58.96,1:35:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember visiting and they had disassembled the great stained glass window.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:04.96,1:35:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And were cleaning it.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:06.96,1:35:09.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It hadn't been cleaned in 500 years or something.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:09.96,1:35:12.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And they clean it every 500 years whether it needs it or not.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:15.18,1:35:21.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And it costs over one million dollars to disassemble that giant stained glass window.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:21.18,1:35:27.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Disassemble it from the lead and clean each little piece of glass and put it back again.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:27.31,1:35:31.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And that in itself is reverence, is it not?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:31.31,1:35:37.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And when you look, when you visit the great cathedrals you go into an overwhelm.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:37.36,1:35:44.36,Default,,0,0,0,,When you realize that what you're looking at often represents the life work.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:44.36,1:35:51.39,Default,,0,0,0,,One human being spent one entire life carving this, the beautiful carvings around the pulpit.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:51.39,1:35:57.56,Default,,0,0,0,,One entire life carving this beautiful carving around the pulpit.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:57.56,1:36:00.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And that you might say is devotion to God.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:00.56,1:36:05.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Devotion to God in its practical application.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:05.68,1:36:09.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Rather than abstract.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:09.17,1:36:14.17,Default,,0,0,0,,So we avoid all hatred doctrines.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:14.17,1:36:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,We follow the inspiration of music at the great cathedrals and beauty.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:21.28,1:36:26.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And we verify the level of consciousness of our teachers.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:26.28,1:36:33.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And we don't go on glamorization or just reputation or enthusiasm.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:33.31,1:36:35.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, what's the next one?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:35.53,1:36:38.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, religion isn't.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:38.38,1:36:41.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Religion itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:41.56,1:36:45.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Religion gets away with murder all the time.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:45.05,1:36:46.05,Default,,0,0,0,,It really does.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:46.05,1:36:50.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Religion, if you look at it over the centuries, it's been hijacked.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:50.05,1:36:53.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Hijacked by politicians.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:53.05,1:36:57.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And very often religion is then used.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:57.18,1:37:00.18,Default,,0,0,0,,It's really become a political.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:00.18,1:37:02.18,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a politic, not a religion.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:02.18,1:37:07.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Our intention helps us to stay on the straight and narrow.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:07.32,1:37:09.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Various religious practices.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:09.73,1:37:17.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Tend to reinforce our spiritual dedication.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:17.02,1:37:20.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The practice of the great virtues.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:20.02,1:37:23.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The practice of the great commandments.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:23.02,1:37:26.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The avoidance of the deadly sins.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:26.22,1:37:32.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And the de-glamorization of that which is of passing attractions.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:32.53,1:37:39.85,Default,,0,0,0,,So our idea is how can we stay on course in a world which is dedicated.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:39.85,1:37:42.85,Default,,0,0,0,,To the glamorization of falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:42.85,1:37:43.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:44.27,1:37:46.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Practical spirituality.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:46.27,1:37:51.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Basic to it is our own goodwill.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:51.38,1:37:53.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Goodwill towards life.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:53.80,1:37:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Goodwill towards all that lives.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:56.80,1:38:01.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Sensitivity to the beauty of all that exists.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:01.85,1:38:04.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Avoid the ancient mysteries.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:04.85,1:38:08.85,Default,,0,0,0,,It's always somebody poking around through ancient mysteries.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:08.85,1:38:14.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Ancient mysteries uncovered in the tombs.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:14.19,1:38:20.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And there was a period of time where I visited all those things.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:20.89,1:38:24.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Myself to verify them.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:24.13,1:38:29.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I got to see the sarcophagus of great beings.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:29.15,1:38:32.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And I got to meditate in the great pyramids.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:32.28,1:38:35.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Spent all night meditating in the great pyramids.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:35.38,1:38:40.14,Default,,0,0,0,,How can you get a whole pyramid to yourself?
Dialogue: 0,1:38:40.14,1:38:42.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It was ten bucks I think.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:42.14,1:38:44.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It was ten bucks I think.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:44.72,1:38:45.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It was ten bucks.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:45.72,1:38:50.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I said to the guard.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:50.61,1:38:53.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to meditate there all night.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:53.61,1:38:58.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And his hand almost automatically went like this.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:58.42,1:39:00.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I crossed his palm with silver.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:00.42,1:39:02.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I think ten bucks or five.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:02.57,1:39:04.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I forget which.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:04.67,1:39:07.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And he stood guard at the door to the pyramid.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:07.73,1:39:11.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And by God I had an entire pyramid to myself the entire night.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:11.73,1:39:14.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I could study.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:14.02,1:39:18.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I could meditate all night long with the whole pyramid all my own.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:18.02,1:39:21.47,Default,,0,0,0,,How many people get a whole pyramid just to itself?
Dialogue: 0,1:39:21.47,1:39:26.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought that was a great opportunity.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:26.60,1:39:32.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And it was a very cannot be described kind of a night.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:32.72,1:39:35.81,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:35.81,1:39:40.93,Default,,0,0,0,,So we want to avoid high price gurus with specialness.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:40.93,1:39:44.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Friends of mine were spiritual seekers.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:44.93,1:39:47.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And they made the rounds of all.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:47.93,1:39:52.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Or many of the very well known gurus.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:52.97,1:39:56.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And what it cost them.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:56.01,1:39:59.01,Default,,0,0,0,,It cost them at a return.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:59.01,1:40:00.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:00.01,1:40:04.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And so avoid high price gurus.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:04.22,1:40:05.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:05.22,1:40:07.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Especially when they are.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:07.22,1:40:10.22,Default,,0,0,0,,They note themselves to be special.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:10.22,1:40:12.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:12.71,1:40:17.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Avoid the evil of the seduction by glamour.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:17.26,1:40:18.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think evil.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:18.64,1:40:21.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think evil is the right word there.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:21.64,1:40:25.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I just say avoid the seduction by glamour.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:25.69,1:40:27.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The glamourization.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:27.69,1:40:34.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And I notice many of the so-called spiritual teachers who calibrate extremely low.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:34.53,1:40:37.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on with sort of a theatrical glamour.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:37.53,1:40:41.53,Default,,0,0,0,,You always have to have the sandals or the bare feet and the long robe.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:41.53,1:40:44.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And a big cross hanging around your neck.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:44.92,1:40:47.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And holy signs hanging off of you.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:50.14,1:40:56.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually a true spiritual teacher probably looks more like a business man than anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:56.52,1:40:59.68,Default,,0,0,0,,He's got a shirt and a tie on.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:59.68,1:41:07.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So you want to avoid that which is fallacious and special.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:07.35,1:41:11.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And you want to avoid the seduction by glamour.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:11.35,1:41:18.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Glamourization means exaggeration of that which is ordinarily considered attractive in our world.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:18.47,1:41:22.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course in miracles I recommend to people.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:22.76,1:41:24.76,Default,,0,0,0,,People rather generally.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:24.76,1:41:28.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it sets you to an inner direction.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:28.76,1:41:31.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not beholden to anyone.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:31.89,1:41:37.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you check it out you'll see that it calibrates at 600.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:37.07,1:41:40.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And the workbook calibrates at 550 or so.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:40.07,1:41:45.07,Default,,0,0,0,,But I think the workbook of A Course in Miracles calibrates at 600.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:45.07,1:41:46.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I forget now.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:46.07,1:41:47.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to make sure.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:47.14,1:41:49.14,Default,,0,0,0,,The workbook of A Course in Miracles.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:49.14,1:41:51.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I have permission to ask.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:51.14,1:41:52.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Calibrates at 600.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:52.14,1:41:54.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Calibrates at 600.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:54.14,1:41:55.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:55.14,1:41:57.14,Default,,0,0,0,,The workbook of A Course in Miracles.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:57.14,1:42:04.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So people say well I don't know where to go for spiritual teaching or teachers or congregations or something.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:04.14,1:42:06.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I think go to church.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:06.34,1:42:10.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Go to church and study A Course in Miracles.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:10.34,1:42:13.34,Default,,0,0,0,,That combination should do it for everybody.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:13.34,1:42:14.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:14.34,1:42:17.39,Default,,0,0,0,,How many people here have been A Course in Miracles?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:17.39,1:42:18.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:18.39,1:42:19.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh pretty good.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:19.39,1:42:20.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank God.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:20.39,1:42:21.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank goodness I'm saved.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:22.39,1:42:26.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:26.39,1:42:29.56,Default,,0,0,0,,A Course in Miracles people are safe to be around.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:29.56,1:42:31.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Safe to be around.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:31.68,1:42:34.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's a fantastic experience.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:34.68,1:42:37.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Especially when the so-called cities hit you.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:37.68,1:42:41.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You do A Course in Miracles and all of a sudden the miraculous begins to occur.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:41.68,1:42:44.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's rather jarring in the beginning.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:44.97,1:42:49.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You begin to think the thing and it happens.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:49.46,1:42:51.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I use it at home.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:51.46,1:42:52.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It's very practical.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:52.46,1:42:58.84,Default,,0,0,0,,We've got one cat that has to have something put in his eye all the time and we never can find the cat.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:58.84,1:43:01.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So I ask the Holy Spirit to guide me to the cat and there he is.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:01.84,1:43:04.84,Default,,0,0,0,,He's under the table.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:04.84,1:43:10.31,Default,,0,0,0,,So the Course in Miracles is good for finding lost cats and various things like that.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:10.31,1:43:14.31,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't know what you did with the keys to the car.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:14.31,1:43:20.39,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a lot of glamorization of ancient mysteries.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:20.39,1:43:23.39,Default,,0,0,0,,You see it on television all the time.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:23.39,1:43:24.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And prophecies.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:24.39,1:43:27.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Prophecies of the end of the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:27.39,1:43:31.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And we all know what is the next end of the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:31.68,1:43:33.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I forget, 2012?
Dialogue: 0,1:43:33.68,1:43:41.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody's ready for the next end of the world?
Dialogue: 0,1:43:41.03,1:43:46.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, that's based on the Mayan calendar.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:46.77,1:43:47.77,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right, I forgot.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:47.77,1:43:49.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The Mayan calendar.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:49.93,1:43:54.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The world ends in December 2012.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:54.26,1:43:56.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I have the arm.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:56.42,1:43:58.77,Default,,0,0,0,,It's fallacious.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:58.77,1:44:00.31,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:00.31,1:44:02.31,Default,,0,0,0,,So the Mayan calendar is fallacious.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:02.31,1:44:07.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The Mayan calendar is not calibrating mankind.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:07.53,1:44:10.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It's calibrating an era.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:10.53,1:44:17.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So the Mayan calendar calibrates the calendar of a whole end of an era.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:17.53,1:44:23.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So like what we would call the end of a century.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:23.07,1:44:26.07,Default,,0,0,0,,What we call the end of a century doesn't mean the world's going to end.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:26.07,1:44:30.07,Default,,0,0,0,,It just means that our means of keeping track of things
Dialogue: 0,1:44:30.07,1:44:33.07,Default,,0,0,0,,will come to the end at the end of December.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:33.07,1:44:40.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, a miracle leads you back to inner direction.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:40.10,1:44:41.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:41.10,1:44:45.86,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the next one?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:45.86,1:44:54.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Flexibility protects you from making serious errors.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:54.14,1:44:57.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Stores us within of happiness.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:57.68,1:45:01.89,Default,,0,0,0,,We got rid of that in a hurry, didn't we?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:05.89,1:45:07.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And here's one I made.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:07.89,1:45:11.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Want what you have instead of having what you want.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:11.89,1:45:14.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's a good one.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:14.82,1:45:16.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Just because I made it up, it's excellent.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:19.14,1:45:23.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Want what you have instead of what you want.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:23.14,1:45:27.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Want what you want instead of what you don't have, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:27.92,1:45:31.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Happiness is an inner decision.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:31.27,1:45:34.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And you have to give up self-pity.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:34.56,1:45:36.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:36.26,1:45:38.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:38.85,1:45:42.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want to be happy then.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:42.14,1:45:44.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So I got to give up self-pity.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:44.14,1:45:45.14,Default,,0,0,0,,That's too much.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:47.14,1:45:49.93,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:49.93,1:45:51.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The next one is a really important one
Dialogue: 0,1:45:51.93,1:45:58.31,Default,,0,0,0,,that we can get psychologically adjusted to and get our teeth into.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:58.31,1:46:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Make choices instead of craving, wanting, desiring, clutching.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:04.96,1:46:08.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Choose things instead of craving them.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:08.11,1:46:10.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I choose to be happy.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:10.11,1:46:13.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I choose to buy this new car.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:13.11,1:46:14.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Without craving it.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:14.11,1:46:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Without craving it.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:16.40,1:46:20.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So decide, I'm going to give up all craving-ness.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:20.40,1:46:22.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Craving-ness.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:22.85,1:46:25.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Craving-ness is I cannot be happy unless I have this new hat.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:25.85,1:46:29.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I cannot be happy unless I get to see this movie.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:29.85,1:46:31.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I cannot be happy unless...
Dialogue: 0,1:46:31.85,1:46:35.85,Default,,0,0,0,,So you're putting your happiness on something outside yourself.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:35.85,1:46:42.89,Default,,0,0,0,,So you can't let your ego get away with placing the source of happiness outside yourself.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:42.89,1:46:46.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The source of happiness is only within.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:46.02,1:46:52.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you win a million dollars, the only happiness is that it makes you happy within.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:52.34,1:46:57.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not going to change your life much generally.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:57.46,1:47:00.46,Default,,0,0,0,,People who think a million dollars is going to make a big change in their life
Dialogue: 0,1:47:00.46,1:47:05.46,Default,,0,0,0,,are surprised to find that it makes very little change after all.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:05.46,1:47:06.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:06.59,1:47:10.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Surrender all cravings to God.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:10.55,1:47:14.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever you find yourself craving.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:14.26,1:47:17.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Women and booze.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:17.14,1:47:28.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I got a mug at home when I chose the guy with his thing on him.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:28.22,1:47:31.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Talking to the bartender.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:31.39,1:47:34.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I spent all my money on women and booze.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:34.39,1:47:36.39,Default,,0,0,0,,The rest I wasted.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:44.27,1:47:51.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Eventually, with a spiritual orientation towards life,
Dialogue: 0,1:47:51.78,1:47:56.19,Default,,0,0,0,,you develop a certain joie de vivre.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:56.19,1:47:58.46,Default,,0,0,0,,A certain joy.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:58.46,1:48:03.48,Default,,0,0,0,,A certain joyousness about being alive in the first place.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:03.48,1:48:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And who was the French entertainer asked about that?
Dialogue: 0,1:48:08.48,1:48:11.48,Default,,0,0,0,,When he was asked, how do you feel about being 77?
Dialogue: 0,1:48:11.48,1:48:16.06,Default,,0,0,0,,He said, considering the alternative, very good indeed.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:16.06,1:48:18.56,Default,,0,0,0,,That was that French...
Dialogue: 0,1:48:18.56,1:48:20.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Who was it?
Dialogue: 0,1:48:20.92,1:48:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Maurice Chevalier.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:21.92,1:48:23.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:23.92,1:48:27.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Considering the alternative, I feel very good about being 77.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:27.92,1:48:29.52,Default,,0,0,0,,He says.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:29.52,1:48:35.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So joie de vivre is a certain attitude that is independent of events.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:35.52,1:48:38.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:38.26,1:48:42.93,Default,,0,0,0,,A certain happiness, the joy of life.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:42.93,1:48:46.93,Default,,0,0,0,,One can quickly get there by gratitude for life.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:46.93,1:48:56.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh Lord, I give thanks that I have had this privilege to experience life.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:56.85,1:48:59.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Because for all the millions who are experiencing life,
Dialogue: 0,1:48:59.85,1:49:05.22,Default,,0,0,0,,there are ultra millions who are not.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:05.22,1:49:08.27,Default,,0,0,0,,So we are very fortunate then.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:08.27,1:49:17.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Karmically, we have inherited the gift of experiencing life.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:17.68,1:49:23.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Joie de vivre is independent of events, is a certain attitude.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:23.89,1:49:27.89,Default,,0,0,0,,When we get caught into craving, the thing to ask yourself,
Dialogue: 0,1:49:27.89,1:49:30.89,Default,,0,0,0,,who is it within me that is wanting?
Dialogue: 0,1:49:30.89,1:49:33.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it the child?
Dialogue: 0,1:49:33.42,1:49:34.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to be famous.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:34.42,1:49:35.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:35.42,1:49:38.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it the child that wants to be famous?
Dialogue: 0,1:49:38.42,1:49:40.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The adult?
Dialogue: 0,1:49:40.53,1:49:42.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it the parent?
Dialogue: 0,1:49:42.53,1:49:45.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Who is it in you that wants things?
Dialogue: 0,1:49:45.89,1:49:55.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Very often we'll find it's the child that wants to have their own way.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:55.06,1:49:58.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it the child, the adult, or the parent?
Dialogue: 0,1:49:58.06,1:50:02.93,Default,,0,0,0,,It's always a good thing to ask yourself when you're in any kind of a jam.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:02.93,1:50:07.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Differentiate the actual from that which is symbolic.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:07.06,1:50:12.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Winning or gaining in our world is often symbolized.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:12.06,1:50:14.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Symbolized by a certain address.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:14.06,1:50:17.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Symbolized by a certain car.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:17.06,1:50:20.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Symbolized by a certain title.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:20.26,1:50:22.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Job description.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:22.26,1:50:26.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And these things are all symbolic.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:26.26,1:50:31.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And in and of themselves have no particular worth.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:31.67,1:50:36.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The fact that you're president of the company is very gratifying.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:36.02,1:50:37.50,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:37.50,1:50:39.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So we'll go back to the next one.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:39.50,1:50:45.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Differentiate narcissistic from mature goals.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:45.46,1:50:47.72,Default,,0,0,0,,To become rich and famous.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:47.72,1:50:51.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Becoming rich and famous seems to be the preoccupation of everybody.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:51.72,1:50:57.88,Default,,0,0,0,,When you watch the TV news, the rich and famous parade before the camera.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:57.88,1:51:01.17,Default,,0,0,0,,They do everything to stay in the news.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:01.17,1:51:08.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Commit crimes, violate the parole, repeat the same mistakes over and over again.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:08.17,1:51:15.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Until they don't get any more publicity out of it than they give it up.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:15.17,1:51:23.13,Default,,0,0,0,,If they don't get back on TV by relapsing drugs and getting rearrested, then they give up the drugs.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:23.13,1:51:29.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll say the way to get these movie stars to give up their drugs is to ignore them in the media.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:29.42,1:51:31.42,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, they're back in jail again.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:31.42,1:51:32.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Ignore it.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:32.82,1:51:37.82,Default,,0,0,0,,They will actually get themselves back in jail again so they can get on the news that they're back in jail again.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:37.82,1:51:38.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It's hard to believe.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:38.82,1:51:40.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Do anything to stay in the news.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:40.85,1:51:42.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Stay in the news.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:44.02,1:51:46.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's narcissism.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:46.02,1:51:50.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Be pleased with the direction and alignment of how you are now.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:50.43,1:51:57.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And some people are not satisfied until they have achieved a certain goal.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:57.59,1:52:00.59,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, they're not enjoying the journey.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:00.59,1:52:04.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So you learn to enjoy the journey of life.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:04.72,1:52:06.01,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:06.01,1:52:10.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's say you're seeking enlightenment or at least an advanced state of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:11.17,1:52:15.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And there isn't any, this is no good and this is all good.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:15.17,1:52:24.81,Default,,0,0,0,,The process, the process may take you all around the world, may take you to see and hear certain teachers,
Dialogue: 0,1:52:24.81,1:52:32.13,Default,,0,0,0,,may take you to great cathedrals, may require a sacrifice, walking barefoot across the desert, whatever.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:32.13,1:52:34.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I've told this joke before.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:34.13,1:52:37.18,Default,,0,0,0,,This guy is very enthused about religion.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:37.18,1:52:40.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And so he visits the Holy Land.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:40.53,1:52:43.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And he sees this fisherman out there.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:43.57,1:52:51.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And he says,
Dialogue: 0,1:52:51.81,1:52:53.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And the fisherman looks over at him and he says,
Dialogue: 0,1:52:53.81,1:52:56.81,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you want, sheet face?
Dialogue: 0,1:52:56.81,1:52:59.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I've told that joke before.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:59.02,1:53:09.18,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's because of our, we are enamored of the glamour of religiosity.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:09.18,1:53:12.18,Default,,0,0,0,,We ourselves become glamorized by it.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:12.18,1:53:18.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Be pleased with the direction you're going and not just a goal.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:18.75,1:53:25.17,Default,,0,0,0,,The practical reality versus fantasy and the glamour of success.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:25.17,1:53:29.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Success is an inner, is an inner condition.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:29.35,1:53:32.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Success is an inner condition.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:32.61,1:53:37.61,Default,,0,0,0,,What the world calls success may have little or nothing to do with what you consider it to be.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:37.61,1:53:39.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And vice versa.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:39.61,1:53:42.61,Default,,0,0,0,,You may consider what you have as successful.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:42.61,1:53:47.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Successful in the world completely ignores it and considers that it's nothing at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:47.61,1:53:51.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Choose and make decisions instead of just hoping.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:51.93,1:53:55.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't hope to go to college.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:55.14,1:53:57.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Bust your chops until you get there.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:57.50,1:54:00.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And bust your chops to do the best while you're there.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:00.50,1:54:05.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So, just hoping is not enough.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:05.14,1:54:08.39,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to back it up with effort.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:08.39,1:54:11.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, the next one.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:11.89,1:54:14.05,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,1:54:14.05,1:54:15.05,Default,,0,0,0,,We're breaking for what?
Dialogue: 0,1:54:15.05,1:54:18.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Lunch.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:18.57,1:54:22.51,Default,,0,0,0,,These people want to eat on top of everything else?
Dialogue: 0,1:54:22.51,1:54:23.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Good God.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:23.51,1:54:25.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:25.51,1:54:29.21,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll see you again at what time?
Dialogue: 0,1:54:29.21,1:54:30.39,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,1:54:30.39,1:54:31.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Two o'clock.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:31.39,1:54:32.46,Default,,0,0,0,,What time?
Dialogue: 0,1:54:32.46,1:54:33.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Two o'clock.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:33.46,1:54:34.46,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll see you again at two o'clock.
